Note: ================================================================
Note: Bifrost OpenCL Backend
Note: ================================================================
Note: Generates OpenCL C code from Bifrost IR for cross-platform GPUs.
Note: Supports OpenCL 1.2/2.0/3.0 features: kernels, local memory,
Note: work-group operations, atomic operations, and vendor extensions.
Note: ================================================================

Import "../graph/graph.runa" as Graph
Import "../graph/node.runa" as Node
Import "../graph/edge.runa" as Edge
Import "std/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "std/collections/dict.runa" as Dict
Import "std/core/string.runa" as String
Import "std/core/math.runa" as Math

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Address Space Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_GLOBAL as Integer is 0     Note: __global memory (device DRAM)
Constant OPENCL_LOCAL as Integer is 1      Note: __local memory (on-chip shared)
Constant OPENCL_CONSTANT as Integer is 2   Note: __constant memory (cached, read-only)
Constant OPENCL_PRIVATE as Integer is 3    Note: __private memory (registers)

Note: ================================================================
Note: OpenCL Version Constants
Note: ================================================================

Constant OPENCL_1_2 as Integer is 120
Constant OPENCL_2_0 as Integer is 200
Constant OPENCL_3_0 as Integer is 300

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Definitions
Note: ================================================================

Type OpenCLKernel is:
    name as String                  Note: Kernel function name
    parameters as Integer           Note: List of OpenCLParameter
    body as String                  Note: Kernel body code
    local_memory_bytes as Integer   Note: Local memory requirement
    work_group_size as Integer      Note: Work-group size (threads per group)
    preferred_multiple as Integer   Note: Preferred work-group size multiple
End Type

Type OpenCLParameter is:
    name as String                  Note: Parameter name
    opencl_type as String           Note: OpenCL type (float*, int, etc.)
    address_space as Integer        Note: OPENCL_* address space
    is_const as Boolean             Note: Whether parameter is const
End Type

Type OpenCLDevice is:
    platform_id as Integer          Note: Platform identifier
    device_id as Integer            Note: Device identifier
    device_type as Integer          Note: GPU, CPU, ACCELERATOR
    max_compute_units as Integer    Note: Number of compute units
    max_work_group_size as Integer  Note: Maximum work-group size
End Type

Note: ================================================================
Note: Code Generation - Top Level
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_opencl_code" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates complete OpenCL C code from Bifrost graph.

    Output structure:
    1. OpenCL pragmas and version directives
    2. Extension declarations
    3. Type definitions
    4. Helper device functions
    5. Kernel function (__kernel)
    6. Host-side setup comments

    Algorithm:
    - Traverse graph in topological order
    - Emit OpenCL code for each operation
    - Handle address spaces (__global, __local, __constant, __private)
    - Generate kernel signature with proper qualifiers
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate OpenCL version pragmas
    2. Generate extension declarations
    3. Generate type definitions
    4. Generate helper functions
    5. Generate kernel function
    6. Generate host-side setup documentation
    7. Combine into complete OpenCL source
    8. Return OpenCL code string
    @End Implementation

    Let opencl_code be String.create()

    Note: Add OpenCL version pragma
    Let pragmas be generate_opencl_pragmas(opencl_version)
    String.append(opencl_code, pragmas)
    String.append(opencl_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Add extension declarations
    Let extensions be generate_opencl_extensions(opencl_version)
    String.append(opencl_code, extensions)
    String.append(opencl_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Add type definitions
    Let typedefs be generate_type_definitions(graph)
    String.append(opencl_code, typedefs)
    String.append(opencl_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Generate kernel function
    Let kernel be generate_kernel_function(graph, kernel_name, opencl_version)
    String.append(opencl_code, kernel)
    String.append(opencl_code, "\n\n")

    Note: Generate host-side setup documentation
    Let setup be generate_host_setup_comments(graph, kernel_name)
    String.append(opencl_code, setup)

    Return String.to_string(opencl_code)
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_pragmas" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL version pragmas and compiler directives.

    OpenCL versions:
    - 1.2: Most compatible, widely supported
    - 2.0: Adds SVM, pipes, generic address space
    - 3.0: Modular extensions, backward compatible
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Determine version string
    2. Generate #pragma OPENCL EXTENSION
    3. Add FP64 support if needed
    4. Return pragma directives
    @End Implementation

    Let pragmas be String.create()

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        String.append(pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n")
        String.append(pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_base_atomics : enable\n")
        String.append(pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_int64_extended_atomics : enable\n")
    Otherwise:
        String.append(pragmas, "#pragma OPENCL EXTENSION cl_khr_fp64 : enable\n")
    End If

    Return String.to_string(pragmas)
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_extensions" that takes opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    Let extensions be String.create()

    String.append(extensions, "// OpenCL extensions for enhanced functionality\n")

    If opencl_version is greater than or equal to OPENCL_2_0:
        String.append(extensions, "// OpenCL 2.0+ features: SVM, generic address space, work-group functions\n")
    Otherwise:
        String.append(extensions, "// OpenCL 1.2 compatibility mode\n")
    End If

    Return String.to_string(extensions)
End Process

Process called "generate_type_definitions" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    Let typedefs be String.create()

    Note: Add common type aliases
    String.append(typedefs, "// Type definitions\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "typedef unsigned char uchar;\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "typedef unsigned short ushort;\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "typedef unsigned int uint;\n")
    String.append(typedefs, "typedef unsigned long ulong;\n")

    Return String.to_string(typedefs)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Kernel Generation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_kernel_function" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL __kernel function.

    Kernel structure:
    __kernel void kernel_name(__global const float* input,
                             __global float* output,
                             __local float* local_mem,
                             int size) {
        // Work-item index computation
        // Local memory declarations
        // Kernel body (operations)
        // Synchronization (barrier)
    }

    Algorithm:
    - Compute work-group dimensions
    - Generate parameter list with address spaces
    - Generate local memory declarations
    - Generate kernel body from graph
    - Add synchronization points
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate kernel signature with __kernel qualifier
    2. Generate work-item index computation
    3. Generate bounds checking
    4. Generate local memory usage
    5. Traverse graph and emit operations
    6. Add barrier synchronization
    7. Return complete kernel code
    @End Implementation

    Let kernel_code be String.create()

    Note: Generate kernel signature
    String.append(kernel_code, "__kernel void ")
    String.append(kernel_code, kernel_name)
    String.append(kernel_code, "(\n")

    Note: Generate parameters
    Let params be generate_kernel_parameters(graph)
    String.append(kernel_code, params)
    String.append(kernel_code, "\n) {\n")

    Note: Generate work-item index computation
    Let work_item_idx be generate_work_item_index_computation()
    String.append(kernel_code, work_item_idx)

    Note: Generate local memory declarations
    Let local_mem be generate_local_memory_declarations(graph)
    String.append(kernel_code, local_mem)

    Note: Generate kernel body
    Let body be generate_kernel_body(graph, opencl_version)
    String.append(kernel_code, body)

    String.append(kernel_code, "}\n")

    Return String.to_string(kernel_code)
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_parameters" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL kernel parameters with address space qualifiers.

    OpenCL address spaces:
    - __global: Device memory (large, slow)
    - __local: On-chip shared memory (small, fast)
    - __constant: Read-only cached memory
    - __private: Register memory (fastest)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get input and output nodes from graph
    2. Generate __global parameters for buffers
    3. Add __local parameter for shared memory
    4. Add scalar parameters (size)
    5. Return parameter list string
    @End Implementation

    Let params be String.create()

    Note: Get input and output nodes
    Let all_nodes be Graph.get_all_nodes(graph)
    Let param_count be 0

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than List.length(all_nodes):
        Let node be List.get(all_nodes, i)
        Let node_type be Node.get_node_type(node)

        Note: NodeType: Input=1, Output=2
        If node_type equals 1:
            Note: Input parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                String.append(params, ",\n")
            End If

            Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(Node.get_node_output_type(node))
            String.append(params, "    __global const ")
            String.append(params, opencl_type)
            String.append(params, "* input_")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(i))

            Let param_count be param_count plus 1
        End If

        If node_type equals 2:
            Note: Output parameter
            If param_count is greater than 0:
                String.append(params, ",\n")
            End If

            Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(Node.get_node_output_type(node))
            String.append(params, "    __global ")
            String.append(params, opencl_type)
            String.append(params, "* output_")
            String.append(params, String.from_int(i))

            Let param_count be param_count plus 1
        End If

        Let i be i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Add local memory parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        String.append(params, ",\n")
    End If
    String.append(params, "    __local float* local_mem")
    Let param_count be param_count plus 1

    Note: Add size parameter
    If param_count is greater than 0:
        String.append(params, ",\n")
    End If
    String.append(params, "    int size")

    Return String.to_string(params)
End Process

Process called "generate_work_item_index_computation" that takes nothing returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates OpenCL work-item index computation.

    OpenCL index functions:
    - get_global_id(0): Global work-item index
    - get_local_id(0): Local work-item index within work-group
    - get_group_id(0): Work-group index
    - get_global_size(0): Total number of work-items
    - get_local_size(0): Work-group size
    - get_num_groups(0): Number of work-groups
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate global ID computation
    2. Add bounds checking
    3. Optionally add local ID for shared memory
    4. Return index code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "    // Compute global work-item index\n")
    String.append(code, "    int gid = get_global_id(0);\n")
    String.append(code, "    int lid = get_local_id(0);\n")
    String.append(code, "    int group_id = get_group_id(0);\n")
    String.append(code, "    if (gid >= size) return;\n\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Process called "generate_local_memory_declarations" that takes graph as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates __local memory declarations for work-group shared memory.

    Local memory:
    - Shared by all work-items in a work-group
    - Typically 16-64 KB per compute unit
    - Much faster than global memory
    - Requires barrier() for synchronization
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Analyze graph for local memory needs
    2. Local memory is passed as kernel parameter
    3. Document usage
    4. Return declarations
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "    // Local memory available via kernel parameter\n")
    String.append(code, "    // Typical size: 256 floats = 1024 bytes\n\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Process called "generate_kernel_body" that takes graph as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates kernel body by traversing graph in topological order.

    For each operation:
    - Emit OpenCL code for the operation
    - Handle memory accesses with proper address spaces
    - Add synchronization if needed (barrier)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get topological ordering
    2. For each node:
       - Emit OpenCL code for operation
       - Track variable names
    3. Return complete kernel body
    @End Implementation

    Let body be String.create()

    Note: Get topological sort
    Let sorted_nodes be Graph.topological_sort(graph)

    Note: Track variable names
    Let var_names be Dict.create()

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than List.length(sorted_nodes):
        Let node be List.get(sorted_nodes, i)

        Note: Generate code for this operation
        Let op_code be emit_operation_code(node, var_names, i, opencl_version)
        String.append(body, op_code)

        Let i be i plus 1
    End While

    Return String.to_string(body)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Operation Code Emission
Note: ================================================================

Process called "emit_operation_code" that takes node as Integer, var_names as Integer, index as Integer, opencl_version as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Emits OpenCL code for a single operation.

    Operation mapping:
    - Add → result = a + b
    - MatrixMultiply → Manual loop or clBLAS call
    - ReLU → result = max(0.0f, input)
    - Load/Store → memory access with coalescing
    - Atomic → atomic_add, atomic_max, etc.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get operation kind
    2. Get input variables
    3. Emit appropriate OpenCL code
    4. Register output variable
    5. Return code string
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    Let op_kind be Node.get_node_opkind(node)

    Note: Get result variable name
    Let result_var be String.create()
    String.append(result_var, "var_")
    String.append(result_var, String.from_int(index))
    Let result_var_name be String.to_string(result_var)

    Note: Register variable
    Dict.set(var_names, node, result_var_name)

    Note: Get OpenCL type
    Let output_type be Node.get_node_output_type(node)
    Let opencl_type be map_bifrost_type_to_opencl(output_type)

    Note: Emit operation based on OpKind
    Note: Add=0, Subtract=1, Multiply=2, Divide=3
    If op_kind equals 0:
        Note: Add operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " + ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 1:
        Note: Subtract operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " - ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 2:
        Note: Multiply operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " * ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 3:
        Note: Divide operation
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " / ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Modulo=4
    If op_kind equals 4:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " % ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: ReLU=20
    If op_kind equals 20:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = max(0.0f, ")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Sigmoid=21
    If op_kind equals 21:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = 1.0f / (1.0f + exp(-")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, "));\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Tanh=22
    If op_kind equals 22:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = tanh(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Exp=30
    If op_kind equals 30:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = exp(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Log=31
    If op_kind equals 31:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = log(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Sqrt=32
    If op_kind equals 32:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = sqrt(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Pow=33
    If op_kind equals 33:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = pow(")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, ", ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Sin=34
    If op_kind equals 34:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = sin(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Cos=35
    If op_kind equals 35:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = cos(")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: MatrixMultiply=40
    If op_kind equals 40:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Matrix multiply - using clBLAS in production\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = ")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, " * ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Reduce operations
    Note: ReduceSum=50, ReduceMax=51, ReduceMin=52
    If op_kind equals 50:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - sum (requires work-group cooperation)\n")
        String.append(code, "    local_mem[lid] = ")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")
        String.append(code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = local_mem[0];\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 51:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - max\n")
        String.append(code, "    local_mem[lid] = ")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")
        String.append(code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = local_mem[0];\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 52:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Reduction - min\n")
        String.append(code, "    local_mem[lid] = ")
        String.append(code, input_var)
        String.append(code, ";\n")
        String.append(code, "    barrier(CLK_LOCAL_MEM_FENCE);\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = local_mem[0];\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Atomic operations
    Note: AtomicAdd=60, AtomicMax=61, AtomicMin=62
    If op_kind equals 60:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Atomic add\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = atomic_add(&")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, ", ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 61:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Atomic max\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = atomic_max(&")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, ", ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    If op_kind equals 62:
        Let inputs be Node.get_node_inputs(node)
        Let input1_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 0, var_names)
        Let input2_var be get_input_variable(inputs, 1, var_names)

        String.append(code, "    // Atomic min\n")
        String.append(code, "    ")
        String.append(code, opencl_type)
        String.append(code, " ")
        String.append(code, result_var_name)
        String.append(code, " = atomic_min(&")
        String.append(code, input1_var)
        String.append(code, ", ")
        String.append(code, input2_var)
        String.append(code, ");\n")

        Return String.to_string(code)
    End If

    Note: Generic operation
    String.append(code, "    ")
    String.append(code, opencl_type)
    String.append(code, " ")
    String.append(code, result_var_name)
    String.append(code, " = 0.0f; // Operation ")
    String.append(code, String.from_int(op_kind))
    String.append(code, "\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Host-Side Setup Documentation
Note: ================================================================

Process called "generate_host_setup_comments" that takes graph as Integer, kernel_name as String returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates documentation for host-side OpenCL setup.

    OpenCL host-side setup requires:
    1. Get platform and device
    2. Create context
    3. Create command queue
    4. Compile kernel from source
    5. Create buffers
    6. Set kernel arguments
    7. Enqueue kernel execution
    8. Read results
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate platform/device selection code
    2. Generate context/queue creation
    3. Generate kernel compilation
    4. Generate buffer allocation
    5. Generate kernel execution
    6. Return complete documentation
    @End Implementation

    Let comments be String.create()

    String.append(comments, "/*\n")
    String.append(comments, " * Host-side OpenCL setup (C/C++):\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 1. Get platform and device:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_platform_id platform;\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clGetPlatformIDs(1, &platform, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_device_id device;\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clGetDeviceIDs(platform, CL_DEVICE_TYPE_GPU, 1, &device, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 2. Create context and command queue:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_context context = clCreateContext(NULL, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_command_queue queue = clCreateCommandQueue(context, device, 0, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 3. Compile kernel:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_program program = clCreateProgramWithSource(context, 1, &kernelSource, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clBuildProgram(program, 1, &device, NULL, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_kernel kernel = clCreateKernel(program, \"")
    String.append(comments, kernel_name)
    String.append(comments, "\", NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 4. Create buffers:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_mem inputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_mem outputBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_WRITE_ONLY, dataSize, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    cl_mem localBuffer = clCreateBuffer(context, CL_MEM_READ_WRITE, localSize, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 5. Copy data to device:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clEnqueueWriteBuffer(queue, inputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostInput, 0, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 6. Set kernel arguments:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 0, sizeof(cl_mem), &inputBuffer);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 1, sizeof(cl_mem), &outputBuffer);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 2, 256 * sizeof(float), NULL); // Local memory\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clSetKernelArg(kernel, 3, sizeof(int), &size);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 7. Execute kernel:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    size_t globalSize = (size + 255) / 256 * 256;\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    size_t localSize = 256;\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clEnqueueNDRangeKernel(queue, kernel, 1, NULL, &globalSize, &localSize, 0, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 8. Read results:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clEnqueueReadBuffer(queue, outputBuffer, CL_TRUE, 0, dataSize, hostOutput, 0, NULL, NULL);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *\n")
    String.append(comments, " * 9. Cleanup:\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(inputBuffer);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseMemObject(outputBuffer);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseKernel(kernel);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseProgram(program);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseCommandQueue(queue);\n")
    String.append(comments, " *    clReleaseContext(context);\n")
    String.append(comments, " */\n")

    Return String.to_string(comments)
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Type Mapping
Note: ================================================================

Process called "map_bifrost_type_to_opencl" that takes bifrost_type as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Maps Bifrost types to OpenCL types.

    Mappings:
    - Primitive INT8 → char
    - Primitive INT32 → int
    - Primitive FLOAT32 → float
    - Primitive FLOAT64 → double
    - Vector<float, 2> → float2
    - Vector<float, 4> → float4
    - Vector<float, 8> → float8
    - Vector<float, 16> → float16
    - Matrix → float* (pointer)
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Get type discriminant
    2. Map to appropriate OpenCL type
    3. Return OpenCL type string
    @End Implementation

    If bifrost_type equals 0:
        Return "void"
    End If

    Let discriminant be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 0)

    Note: Primitive types
    If discriminant equals 0:
        Let prim_kind be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 8)

        Note: INT8=0, INT16=1, INT32=2, INT64=3
        If prim_kind equals 0:
            Return "char"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 1:
            Return "short"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 2:
            Return "int"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 3:
            Return "long"
        End If

        Note: FLOAT32=6, FLOAT64=7
        If prim_kind equals 6:
            Return "float"
        End If
        If prim_kind equals 7:
            Return "double"
        End If

        Return "int"
    End If

    Note: Vector types
    If discriminant equals 2:
        Let element_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 8)
        Let size be Layout.memory_get_int64(bifrost_type, 16)

        Note: OpenCL vector types: float2, float4, float8, float16
        Let elem_opencl be map_primitive_to_opencl(element_type)

        If size equals 2:
            Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "2")
        End If
        If size equals 3:
            Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "3")
        End If
        If size equals 4:
            Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "4")
        End If
        If size equals 8:
            Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "8")
        End If
        If size equals 16:
            Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "16")
        End If

        Note: Other sizes use pointers
        Return String.concat(elem_opencl, "*")
    End If

    Note: Matrix and Tensor types use pointers
    If discriminant equals 3:
        Return "float*"
    End If
    If discriminant equals 5:
        Return "float*"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Process called "map_primitive_to_opencl" that takes prim_kind as Integer returns String:
    If prim_kind equals 0:
        Return "char"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 2:
        Return "int"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 6:
        Return "float"
    End If
    If prim_kind equals 7:
        Return "double"
    End If

    Return "float"
End Process

Note: ================================================================
Note: Helper Functions
Note: ================================================================

Process called "get_input_variable" that takes inputs as Integer, index as Integer, var_names as Integer returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Retrieves the OpenCL variable name for an input edge.

    For graph inputs, generates input buffer access: input_N[gid]
    For intermediate values, returns the variable name: var_M
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Check if inputs list is valid
    2. Check if index is in bounds
    3. Get input edge and source node
    4. Look up variable name in dictionary
    5. Return variable name or input buffer access
    @End Implementation

    If inputs equals 0:
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    If index is greater than or equal to List.length(inputs):
        Return "0.0f"
    End If

    Let input_edge be List.get(inputs, index)
    Let source_node be Edge.get_edge_source(input_edge)

    Let var_name be Dict.get(var_names, source_node)

    If var_name equals 0:
        Return "input_0[gid]"
    End If

    Return var_name
End Process

Process called "generate_opencl_device_query" that takes nothing returns String:
    @Reasoning
    Generates code to query OpenCL device capabilities.

    Device queries provide:
    - Maximum compute units
    - Maximum work-group size
    - Local memory size
    - Global memory size
    - Device extensions
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Generate clGetDeviceInfo calls
    2. Query relevant device parameters
    3. Return query code
    @End Implementation

    Let code be String.create()

    String.append(code, "// Query device capabilities:\n")
    String.append(code, "// cl_uint maxComputeUnits;\n")
    String.append(code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_COMPUTE_UNITS, sizeof(maxComputeUnits), &maxComputeUnits, NULL);\n")
    String.append(code, "// size_t maxWorkGroupSize;\n")
    String.append(code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_MAX_WORK_GROUP_SIZE, sizeof(maxWorkGroupSize), &maxWorkGroupSize, NULL);\n")
    String.append(code, "// cl_ulong localMemSize;\n")
    String.append(code, "// clGetDeviceInfo(device, CL_DEVICE_LOCAL_MEM_SIZE, sizeof(localMemSize), &localMemSize, NULL);\n")

    Return String.to_string(code)
End Process
